      • initializeWithApiKey

        public static void initializeWithApiKey(android.content.Context context,
                        java.lang.String apiKey,
                        java.lang.String appUid)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Authenticates the api key and application uid of your application.

        This must be called before your application uses built.io sdk.
        You can find your application key and application uid from web.

        Parameters:
        context - Application context.
        apiKey - Application api Key of your application on built.io.
        appUid - Application uid of your application on built.io.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
